  "response_text": "# Budget-Friendly Gluten-Free Meal Plan\n\n## Naturally Gluten-Free Staples (Cheapest Options)\n\n**Grains & Starches:**\n- Rice (bulk white/brown rice)\n- Potatoes and sweet potatoes\n- Corn (polenta, cornmeal)\n- Oats (certified GF if needed, or skip—naturally GF but often cross-contaminated)\n- Beans and lentils\n\n**Proteins:**\n- Eggs\n- Canned tuna/sardines\n- Chicken (buy whole or on sale)\n- Ground meat (cheaper cuts)\n- Dried beans/lentils\n- Peanut butter\n\n**Produce:**\n- Seasonal vegetables (carrots, cabbage, onions, frozen mixed veggies)\n- Bananas, apples, oranges\n- Canned vegetables/fruit (no added sugar)\n\n## Sample Weekly Plan\n\n**Breakfasts:** Eggs, oatmeal, rice porridge, bananas with peanut butter\n\n**Lunches:** Rice + beans + salsa, baked potatoes + canned tuna, lentil soup\n\n**Dinners:** Chicken + rice + vegetables, ground meat tacos (corn tortillas), bean chili\n\n**Snacks:** Hard-boiled eggs, fruit, popcorn (plain, air-popped)\n\n## Money-Saving Tips\n\n- Buy store brands (usually cheaper and naturally GF)\n- Check labels for hidden gluten—most whole foods don't contain it\n- Buy in bulk\n- Avoid pre-made \"gluten-free\" products entirely\n\nWould you like specific recipes or help with a shopping list?",
